results.name: Number of divisors of the n-th prime signature number (A025487(n)).
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: If A025487(n)'s canonical factorization into prime powers is Product p^e(p), then a(n) = Product (e(p) + 1).
example: a(4)=4 because 4 positive integers divide evenly into A025487(4)=6: 1, 2, 3 and 6.
xref: For the number of divisors of n, see A000005.
a(n) = sum of the n-th row of A146290, A146292.
